Whats interactive rebase?

Interactive rebase lets you rewrite Git history.

Run: git rebase -i <commit-hash>

You can reorder, squash, edit, or drop commits.

Useful for cleaning commit history before pushing.

What problem does it solve?

Interactive rebase solves these problems:

Messy commit history with too many small or unclear commits.

Wrong or unclear commit messages.

Commits made in the wrong order.

Need to combine related commits (squash) into one.

Removing mistakes or unnecessary commits before sharing.
